What you need to know:  CAÂ will from July ban the sale of Internet-connecting devices such as mobile phones, computers, printers, and scanners that do not have the capability for the new Internet Protocol version 6 (IPv6).Devices that do not have IPv6 capability will be barred from clearance on the TradeNet, said the communications regulator.The system gives traders and all stakeholders a single access point for all external trade-related services and is accessed by the KRA, KPA and Kebs.